    • Constructor Detail

      • PaymentMethod

        public PaymentMethod(java.lang.String id,
                     long maxTradePeriod,
                     @NotNull
                     org.bitcoinj.core.Coin maxTradeLimit)
        Parameters:
        id - against charge back risk. If Bank do the charge back quickly the Arbitrator and the seller can push another double spend tx to invalidate the time locked payout tx. For the moment we set all to 0 but will have it in place when needed.
        maxTradePeriod - The min. period a trader need to wait until he gets displayed the contact form for opening a dispute.
        maxTradeLimit - The max. allowed trade amount in Bitcoin for that payment method (depending on charge back risk)
